## What Changed

16/18 fleet spokes had silently broken hooks because `$CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR` (and similar env vars) are never resolved by Claude Code when executing hook commands in `settings.json`. The hooks appeared configured but never fired. Health checks passed falsely because the hook script path itself was invalid.

**Fix:** All hook commands in `settings.json` must use absolute paths. Never use `$VAR` or `${VAR}` syntax.

```json
// WRONG — silently broken
"command": "$CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR/.claude/hooks/session-start.sh"

// RIGHT
"command": "/home/mario/projects/myspoke/.claude/hooks/session-start.sh"
```

**Audit command:**
```bash
grep -n '\$[A-Z_]' .claude/settings.json
```
If any matches: replace with absolute paths.

## Why It Matters

Hooks are the backbone of WAI session management (wakeup, guards, track, compaction). A broken hook fails silently — no error, no warning. The spoke appears healthy but runs completely unguarded. Discovery requires active inspection, not passive monitoring.

## Prerequisites

```bash
grep -n '\$[A-Z_]' .claude/settings.json | head -10
```
If output is empty: already clean, skip. If any matches: apply fix.

## CLAUDE.md Anti-Pattern to Add

```
**Hook path variables:** Never use `$CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR` or other assumed env vars in
settings.json hook commands. Always use absolute `/home/<user>/` paths. Unresolved vars
silently break every tool call in the session.
```

## Batch Sequence

- **Apply order:** 1
- **Depends on:** None
- **Parallel-safe:** Yes
